 4 | pages = 707\u2013784 | doi = 10.1017/S0140525X00081061 | citeseerx = 10.1.1.116.4044 | access-date = 2005-12-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20051123085422/http://www.bbsonline.org/documents/a/00/00/04/99/index.html | archive-date = 2005-11-23 | url-status = dead }}\n*{{Cite book  | last1 = Sampson, Geoffrey | title = Evolutionary language understanding | date = 1996 | publisher = Cassell | location = London; New York | isbn = 978-0-304-33650-0 | oclc = 832369870 | authorlink1 = Geoffrey Sampson }}\n*{{Cite book  | last1 = Steels, Luc| title = Grounding symbols through evolutionary language games |editor=Angelo Cangelosi |editor2=Domenico Parisi| work = Simulating the evolution of language | date = 2002 | publisher = Springer | location = London; New York | isbn = 978-1-85233-428-4 | oclc =  47824669| authorlink1 = Luc Steels }}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.emergent-languages.org/ Agent-Based Models of Language Evolution]\n*[http://arti.vub.ac.be/ ARTI Artificial Intelligence Laboratory, Vrije Universiteit Brussel]\n*[http://cnl.psych.cornell.edu/evo_pub.html Cognitive Neuroscience Laboratory]\n*[http://www.elinguistics.net/ Computerized comparative linguistics]\n*[http://www.fcg-net.org/ Fluid Construction Grammar]\n*[http://groups.lis.illinois.edu/amag/langev/ Language Evolution and Computation Bibliography]\n*[http://www.ling.ed.ac.uk/lec/ Language Evolution and Computation Research Unit, University of Edinburgh]\n\n{{Animal communication}}\n{{Evolutionary psychology}}\n{{Portal bar|Language|Linguistics}}\n\n[[Category:Evolution of language]]\n[[Category:Applied linguistics]]\n", "name_user": "Jamesmcmahon0", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: approches \u2192 approaches", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolutionary_linguistics"}
{"title_page": "List of Old Bedford Modernians", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n[[File:Harpur Window.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The Harpur Window, [[Bedford Modern School]]. ''They Shall Mount Up With Wings As Eagles'']]\n\nThe following is a list of some notable '''Old Bedford Modernians''' who are former pupils of [[Bedford Modern School]] in [[Bedford]], England.  At the school, alumni are known as '''OBMs'''.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bedmod.co.uk/obms/|title=OBMs|website=Bedford Modern School}}</ref>  The Old Bedford Modernians' Club was founded in 1892.<ref name=\"auto3\"/>\n\n==Academic and educational==\n[[File:William A. Tilden by Harry H. Salomon.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[William A. Tilden|Sir William Tilden FRS]]]]\n[[File:John Holland Rose.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Holland Rose|Prof. John Holland Rose FBA]]]]\n[[File:Sir Peter Knight and Dr Andrew Miller (7985176466).jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Peter Knight (scientist)|Sir Peter Knight FRS]]]]\n[[File:Peter Wothers portrait by Nathan Pitt.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Peter Wothers|Dr. Peter Wothers MBE]]]]\n* [[William Augustus Tilden|Sir William Augustus Tilden]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (1842\u20131926), Chemist & Dean, [[Royal College of Science]], London<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\">{{Cite book|title=Bedford Modern School of the black & red|work=worldcat.org|isbn=9780950760803|year=1981|oclc = 16558393}}</ref>\n* [[Joseph Reynolds Green|Professor Joseph Reynolds Green]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (1848\u20131914), Professor of Botany to the [[Pharmaceutical Society of Great Britain]]<ref>''The Eagle'', The Magazine of [[Bedford Modern School]], Vol. III (1888), p. 243</ref><ref>''The Eagle'' Vol. XXVII, no. 2 (1949), p. 135</ref>\n* [[William Hillhouse|Professor William Hillhouse]] [[Linnean Society of London|FLS]] (1850\u20131910), first Professor of Botany at the [[University of Birmingham]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Edward Mann Langley]] (1851\u20131933), founded the [[Mathematical Gazette]], created [[Langley\u2019s Adventitious Angles]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[William Robert Bousfield]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (1854\u20131943), [[Physical chemistry|chemist]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[John Holland Rose|Professor John Holland Rose]] [[Fellow of the British Academy|FBA]] (1855\u20131942), [[Vere Harmsworth Professor of Imperial and Naval History]], [[University of Cambridge]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[George Charles Crick]] [[Geological Society of London|FGS]] [[Royal Geographical Society|FRGS]] [[Zoological Society of London|FZS]] (1856\u20131917), geologist, authority on [[Cephalopod]]a, 1st Assistant at the [[Natural History Museum, London|Natural History Museum]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhm.ac.uk/research-curation/library/archives/catalogue/dserve.exe?dsqServer=placid&dsqIni=Dserve.ini&dsqApp=Archive&dsqDb=Persons&dsqSearch=Code==%27PX174%27&dsqCmd=Show.tcl|title=Natural History Museum Archive Catalogue|work=nhm.ac.uk|accessdate=29 April 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur John Pressland]] [[Royal Society of Edinburgh|FRSE]] (1865 \u20131934), educational theorist, linguist, schoolmaster and writer<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Harpur Trust, 1552-1973.|publisher=|isbn=9780950291703|year=1973|oclc = 903515}}</ref>\n* [[George James Gibbs]] [[Royal Astronomical Society|FRAS]] (1866\u20131947), astronomer, engineer, inventor and public science lecturer<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1093/mnras/109.1.1 |title=Meeting of 1949 January 14 |journal=Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society |volume=109 |pages=1\u20132 |year=1949 |last1=Greaves |first1=W. M. H. }}</ref>\n* [[Richard John Durley|Professor Richard John Durley]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (1868\u20131948), Professor of Mechanical Engineering at [[McGill University]] (1901\u201312)<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1680/IJOTI.1948.13374 |title=Obituary. Richard John Durley, 1868-1948 |journal=Journal of the Institution of Civil Engineers |volume=31 |issue=2 |pages=183 |year=1948 }}</ref>\n* [[Laxton Brothers|Edward Augustine Lowe Laxton]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (1869\u20131951), expert on fruit production (''[[Laxton's Superb]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Professor Henry Payne]] [[Royal Aeronautical Society|FRAeS]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|M.Inst.C.E.]] (1871\u20131945), Professor of Engineering at the [[University of Melbourne]]<ref>{{Cite book|chapter-url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/payne-henry-7989|title=Biography \u2013 Henry Payne \u2013 Australian Dictionary of Biography|work=anu.edu.au|accessdate=29 January 2015|chapter=Payne, Henry (1871\u20131945)|publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University}}</ref>\n* [[Jannion Steele Elliott]] (1871\u20131942), [[ornithology|ornithologist]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britishbirds.co.uk/article/obituary-jannion-steele-elliott-1871-1942/|title=Obituary: Jannion Steele Elliott (1871\u20131942)|work=British Birds|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Eric Temple Bell|Dr Eric Temple Bell]], (1883\u20131960), mathematician who specialised in [[number theory]] and formulated the [[Bell series]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=aoctKmbvtMYC&pg=PA354&lpg=PA354&dq=edward+mann+langley+alumni#v=onepage&q=edward%20mann%20langley%20alumni|title=The Search for E. T. Bell|accessdate=29 January 2015|isbn=9780883855089|year=1993|last1=Reid|first1=Constance}}</ref>\n* [[Charles Oatley|Sir Charles Oatley]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]], [[Royal Society|FRS]] [[FREng]] (1904\u20131996), pioneered the development of the [[scanning electron microscope]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/obituary-professor-sir-charles-oatley-1343206.html|title=Obituary: Professor Sir Charles Oatley|work=The Independent|accessdate=29 January 2015|date=1996-03-21}}</ref>\n* [[Gerald Dunning|Dr. G.C. Dunning]], [[Doctor of Letters|D.Lit]], [[Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London|FSA]] (1905\u20131978), pioneering medieval archaeologist, authority on Anglo-Saxon and medieval ceramics<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Dr. G.C. Dunning'', ''Work on Medieval Pottery'', 28 April 1978, p.18</ref><ref>A.Underwood, ''School of the Black and Red. A history of Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, 2010 edn.), p. 130</ref>\n* [[William Francis Grimes|Professor William Francis Grimes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1905\u20131988), Professor of Archaeology, [[University of London]] (1956\u20131973)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Francis MacCarthy Willis Bund|Reverend Francis MacCarthy Willis Bund]] (1906\u20131980), Chaplain, [[Dean (education)|Dean]] and [[Fellow]] of [[Balliol College, Oxford]]<ref>A. Underwood ''The School of the Black and Red''(Bedord, 2010 edn.) p. 284</ref>\n* [[D. C. Riddy|Dr D. C. Riddy]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1907\u20131979), Controller-General of the Education Branch, [[Allied Commission|Control Commission for German \u2013 British Element]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[F.G. Emmison]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] [[Society of Antiquaries of London|FSA]] [[Historical Society|FRHistS]] (1907\u20131995), archivist, author and historian<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxforddnb.com/index/60/101060381/|title=Frederick Emmison|work=oxforddnb.com|accessdate=29 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[J.P.C. Roach|Professor John Roach]] (1920 \u2013 2015), historian<ref name=\"google.co.uk\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=eNo9AAAAYAAJ&dq=educated+bedford+modern+school+new+college+oxford&q=Bedford|title=Essays to a young teacher|year=1966|last1=Howat|first1=Gerald Malcolm David}}</ref>\n* [[Ramsay Shearman|Professor Ramsay Shearman]] DSc [[Fellow of the Royal Academy of Engineering|FReng]] [[Fellow of the Institution of Engineering and Technology|FIET]] [[Royal Meteorological Society|FRMetS]] [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers|FIEEE]] (1924-2019), shortwave radio and radar pioneer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/ramsay-shearman-obituary-98llh6w0j|title=Ramsay Shearman obituary|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Brian Gl\u00fcss|Professor Brian Gl\u00fcss]] [[Royal Statistical Society|FRSS]] (1930\u20132013), statistician, mathematician, systems engineer, author and expert on [[survivor guilt]]<ref>Obituary, ''Dr Brian Gl\u00fcss'', ''Eagle News'', The Magazine of the [[Bedford Modern School|Old Bedford Modernians' Club]], New Series, Volume 6, Number 3 (Issue 110), January 2015</ref>\n* [[John Richard Anthony Pearson|Professor John Richard Anthony Pearson]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] [[Institute of Materials, Minerals and Mining|FIMMM]] [[Institution of Chemical Engineers|MIChemE]] (born 1930), pioneer in [[fluid mechanics]]<ref name=\"auto2\">{{Cite web|url=https://global.oup.com/academic/product/whos-who-and-who-was-who-9780199540891?cc=mt&lang=en&|title=Who's Who and Who Was Who: For autobiographical information on the noteworthy & famous.|publisher=Oxford University Press|via=Oxford University Press}}</ref>\n* [[D.J. Bartholomew|Professor David John Bartholomew]] [[Fellow of the British Academy|FBA]] (1931-2017), Professor of Statistics at the [[London School of Economics|LSE]] (1973\u201396)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\">''School of the Black And Red'' by Andrew Underwood 1981. Reset and updated by Peter Boon, Paul Middleton and Richard Wildman in 2010</ref>\n* [[Philip Bean|Professor Philip Bean]] (born 1936), Professor of [[Criminology]] at [[Loughborough University]], former President of the [[British Society of Criminology|British Soc. of Criminology]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[George Richard Pickett|Professor George Richard Pickett]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (born 1939), Professor of [[Cryogenics|Low Temperature Physics]] at [[Lancaster University]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Sid Gray|Professor Sid Gray]] PhD [[FASSA]] [[Chartered Certified Accountant|FCCA]] (born 1942), Professor at the [[University of Sydney Business School]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sydney.edu.au/business/staff/sgray|title=Sid Gray|work=sydney.edu.au|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Richard Britnell|Professor Richard Hugh Britnell]] [[Fellow of the British Academy|FBA]] (1944\u20132013), Professor of History at [[Durham University]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/education/2013/dec/26/richard-britnell|title=Richard Britnell obituary|first=Christopher|last=Dyer|date=26 December 2013|publisher=|accessdate=30 June 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n* [[Peter Knight (scientist)|Sir Peter Knight]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (born 1947), Professor of [[quantum optics]] at [[Imperial College London]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/20603/Peter-Leonard-KNIGHT|title=Prof Sir Peter Knight, FRS Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Stephen Wildman|Professor Stephen Wildman]] (born 1951), Professor of the History of Art at [[Lancaster University]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Roger Geoffrey Clarke|Dr. Roger Geoffrey Clarke]] (1952\u20132007), [[Ornithology|ornithologist]], world authority on [[Harrier (bird)|harriers]] and other [[Bird of prey|birds of prey]]<ref>Obituary in [[The Times]], 13 February 2007</ref>\n* [[Barry H.V. Topping|Professor Barry H.V. Topping]] [[British Computer Society|MBCS]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|MICE]] [[Institution of Structural Engineers|MIStructE]] [[Institution of Mechanical Engineers|MIMechE]] [[Institute of Mathematics and its Applications|FIMA]] (born 1952), authority and author on [[computational mechanics]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bhvt.org.uk/wwcse.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=22 June 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923184340/http://www.bhvt.org.uk/wwcse.pdf |archive-date=23 September 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[John Clibbens|Professor John Clibbens]] [[Royal Society of Medicine|FRSocMed]] (born 1953), Professor of Developmental Psychology at [[Birmingham City University]]<ref>''The Eagle, The Magazine of Bedford Modern School''</ref>\n* [[Stephen Taylor (economist)|Professor Stephen Taylor]] (born 1953), Professor of Finance at [[Lancaster University]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Richard Janko|Professor Richard Charles Murray Janko]] (born 1955), Professor of Classical Studies at the [[University of Michigan]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Brian Derby|Professor Brian Derby]] [[Institute of Materials, Minerals and Mining|FIMMM]] (born 1956), Professor of [[Materials science]] at [[Manchester University]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Gavin D'Costa|Professor Gavin D'Costa]] (born 1958), Professor in Catholic Theology at the [[University of Bristol]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goanvoice.org.uk/supplement/DrGavinDCosta.htm|title=Goan Voice UK: supplement on : Dr Gavin D'Costa|work=goanvoice.org.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Nick Groom|Professor Nick Groom]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (born 1966), Professor of English Literature at the [[University of Exeter]] and author<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Peter Wothers|Dr Peter David Wothers]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] [[Fellow of the Royal Society of Chemistry|FRSC]] (born 1969), chemist and Fellow of [[St Catharine's College, Cambridge]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\n==Actors, directors and entertainers==\n[[File:GAA0084.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Sessions]]]]\n[[File:Jeremy Irvine 2011.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Jeremy Irvine]]]]\n* [[E.E. Blake]] (1879\u20131961), pioneering exhibitor of motion pictures and owner of cinemas<ref name=\"mocavo.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mocavo.co.uk/International-Motion-Picture-Almanac-1937-38-Volume-1937-38/705462/122|title=International Motion Picture Almanac 1937\u201338|work=Mocavo|accessdate=1 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701093233/http://www.mocavo.co.uk/International-Motion-Picture-Almanac-1937-38-Volume-1937-38/705462/122|archive-date=1 July 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Harrish Ingraham]] (1881\u2013?), Hollywood film director, writer and actor in the era of [[Silent film|silent movies]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mocavo.com/Motion-Picture-Studio-Directory-and-Trade-Annual-1917/271652/92|title=Motion Picture Studio Directory and Trade Annual (1917)|work=Mocavo|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Gillie Potter]] (1887\u20131975), comedian and broadcaster<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1093/ref:odnb/62403 |journal=The Oxford Dictionary of National Biography |year=2004 |title=Potter, Gillie [real name Hugh William Peel] (1887\u20131975), comedian and broadcaster |first1=Si\u00e2n |last1=Nicholas }}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''MR GILLIE POTTER'', ''Comedian of an individual nature'', March 5, 1975, p.16</ref>\n* [[Reginald Berkeley]] (1890\u20131935), playwright and screenwriter in Hollywood (''[[Cavalcade (1933 film)|Cavalcade]]'', ''[[The World Moves On]]'')<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Robert Luff]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1914\u20132009), theatrical agent and producer (''[[The Black and White Minstrel Show]]'')<ref>{{Cite newspaper|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2009/apr/20/robert-luff-obituary-minstrel-show|title=Obituary: Robert Luff|author=Anthony Hayward|journal=The Guardian|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=2009-04-19}}</ref>\n* [[Derek Scott (music director)|Derek Scott]] (1921\u20132006), [[double act]] (with [[Terry-Thomas]] and [[Tony Hancock]]) and music director (''[[The Muppet Show]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestage.co.uk/people/obituaries/2006/07/derek-scott/|title=Derek Scott|work=The Stage|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=2006-07-10}}</ref>\n* [[David Tringham]] (born 1935), [[Film director|assistant film director]] (''[[Lawrence of Arabia (film)|Lawrence of Arabia]]'', ''[[Highlander (film)|Highlander]]'', ''[[Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://literature.proquestlearning.com/critRef/displayItemById.do?QueryType=reference&forAuthor=26221&BackTo=Author%20Page&ItemID=bio26221%20pqllit_ref_lib|title=Full Document \u2013 ProQuest Learning: Literature|work=proquestlearning.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Hugh Armstrong (actor)|Hugh Armstrong]] (1944-2016), actor (''[[How to Get Ahead in Advertising]]'', ''[[Death Line]]'')<ref>Obituary in ''Eagle News'', The Magazine of the [[Bedford Modern School|Old Bedford Modernians' Club]], Issue 113, Summer 2016, p.24</ref>\n* [[David Firth (actor)|David Firth]] (born 1945), actor (''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'', ''[[Midsomer Murders]]''), screenwriter (''[[Home James!]]''), singer (original cast of ''[[The Phantom of the Opera (1986 musical)|Phantom of the Opera]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/16258/David%3B-%3Ei%3Cn%26%23233%3B%3Er%3C-David-Coleman-FIRTH|title=David Firth, Esq Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref> \n* [[John Sessions]] (born 1953), actor (''[[Gangs of New York]]'', ''[[The Iron Lady (film)|The Iron Lady]]'', ''[[Filth (film)|Filth]]''), comedian and broadcaster (''[[QI]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[Julian Hector]] (born 1960), Head of the [[BBC Natural History Unit]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bristol.ac.uk/pace/graduation/honorary-degrees/hondeg14/hector.html|title=Bristol University \u2013 Public and Ceremonial Events Office \u2013 Dr Julian Hector|work=bristol.ac.uk|accessdate=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Saul Nass\u00e9]] (born 1965), producer for the [[BBC]] (''[[Tomorrow's World]]''), CEO at [[Cambridge English Language Assessment]]<ref>''Millennium Eagle'', Magazine of [[Bedford Modern School]], Winter 1999, reprinted (with amendments) August 2004, p.42</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are/our-leadership/saul-nasse/|title=Saul Nass\u00e9|publisher=|accessdate=3 March 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Russell Barnes]] (born 1968), television producer (''[[The Enemies of Reason]]'', ''[[The Genius of Charles Darwin]]'')<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[David Jubb (theatre director)|David Jubb]] (born 1970), theatre director and chief executive of the [[Battersea Arts Centre]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/23491/David-JUBB |title=David Jubb, Esq Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today |work=debretts.com |accessdate=29 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110041050/http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/23491/David-JUBB |archivedate=10 November 2014 }}</ref><ref>''[[Who's Who (UK)|Who's Who]]'', Published by [[A & C Black]], 2020, online edition</ref>\n* [[Russell Howard]] (born 1980), comedian and presenter (''[[Russell Howard's Good News]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/55201/Russell-Joseph-HOWARD|title=Mr Russell Howard Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://russell-magic-cock-howard.tumblr.com/russellhoward|title=Russell Howard's Fruity Fansite|publisher=|accessdate=25 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oAM7DwAAQBAJ&pg=PP3&dq=debrett's+people+of+today+2017#v=onepage&q=russell+howARD|title=People of Today 2017|first=Lucy|last=Hume|date=5 October 2017|publisher=Debrett's|via=Google Books|isbn=9781999767037}}</ref>\n* [[Leon Parris]] (born 1981), writer, composer, musician and actor (''[[Wolfboy]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/education/education-news/education-rise-of-the-fallen-1187285.html|title=Education: Rise of 'The Fallen'|work=The Independent|accessdate=30 January 2015|date=1998-11-26}}</ref>\n* [[Jeremy Irvine]] (born 1990), UK and Hollywood actor (''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]'', ''[[Now Is Good]]'', ''[[Great Expectations (2012 film)|Great Expectations]]'', ''[[The Railway Man (film)|The Railway Man]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordshire-news.co.uk/horsing-talented-blockbuster-role-student-landed/story-21735089-detail/story.html|title=There is no horsing around for talented a blockbuster role student who landed|work=Bedfordshire News|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Sope Dirisu]] (born 1991), stage, television and film actor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedmod.co.uk/2016/04/21/show-business-success-for-obms/|title=Show business success for OBMs|work=Bedford Modern|date=2016-04-21}}</ref>\n* [[Suhani Gandhi]] (born 1994), model and actress<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bedfordtoday.co.uk/news/community-news/talented-student-s-passage-to-india-1-5863917|title=Talented student's passage to India|work=bedfordtoday.co.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Adventurers, aviators, exiles and prisoners of war==\n[[File:John Percy Farrar.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Percy Farrar|Capt. Percy Farrar DSO FGS]]]]\n* [[John Percy Farrar]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1857\u20131929), soldier, mountaineer, President of the [[Alpine Club]], Member of the [[Mount Everest Committee]]<ref name=\"auto\">H.E. Vipan, ''Register of the Old Boys of Bedford Modern School''</ref><ref>Obituary in the ''Bedfordshire Times'', 22 February 1929, p.9</ref>\n* [[Sir Reginald Wolseley, 10th Baronet]] (1872\u20131933), dubbed the elevator [[baronet]]<ref>Kelly's Handbook to the Titled, Landed and Official Classes, Published 1928</ref>\n* [[Henry Evered Haymes|Captain and Bimbashi Henry Haymes]] [[Venerable Order of St John|SBStJ]] [[Royal College of Surgeons|MRCS]] [[LRCP]] (1872\u20131904), surgeon, an original explorer of the [[Bahr el Ghazal (region of South Sudan)|Bahr-el-Ghazal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnw.co.uk/auction-archive/catalogue-archive/lot.php?auction_id=230&lot_id=77178|title=Lot 31, The Allan and Janet Woodliffe Collection of Medals... (18 May 2011) \u2013 Dix Noonan Webb|work=dnw.co.uk|accessdate=30 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141223142200/http://www.dnw.co.uk/auction-archive/catalogue-archive/lot.php?auction_id=230&lot_id=77178|archive-date=23 December 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* [[George E.M. Kelly]] (1878\u20131911), early aviator in the [[Aeronautical Division, US Signal Corps]]<ref name=\"auto\"/> \n* [[Aeneas Mackintosh|Captain Aeneas Lionel Acton Mackintosh]] (1879\u20131916), [[Heroic Age of Antarctic Exploration|Antarctic explorer]], commander of the [[Ross Sea party]] expedition<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[W.A.B. Goodall]] (1880\u20131941), [[castaway]], described as 'the ruler of the world's tiniest kingdom': [[Pulau Sarimbun]], [[Straits of Johore]]<ref>H.E. Vipan, ''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. 47</ref> \n* [[Duncan Alexander Eliott Mackintosh]] (1884\u20131966), 31st Chief of [[Chattan Confederation|Clan Chattan]] (1942\u201366)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepeerage.com/p45058.htm|title=- Person Page 45058|work=thepeerage.com|accessdate=19 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfrid Thomas Reid]] [[Royal Aeronautical Society|FRAeS]] (1887\u20131968), aircraft designer and a pioneer of the Canadian aircraft industry<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n* [[P.C.B. Newington]] (1888\u20131964), author of a [[Cookbook|cookbook]] celebrating Malaysian food, conceived while starving as a [[prisoner of war]]<ref name=\"google.com4\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vJcZAAAAMAAJ&dq=He+was+educated+at+Bedford+Modern+School&q=philip+Newington|title=Malaysia|accessdate=13 November 2015|year=1964}}</ref>\n* [[Frederick Williamson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1891\u20131935), explorer, founder member of the Himalayan Club<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Dick Howe|Captain Richard 'Dick' Howe]] [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1916\u20131981), Escape Officer at [[Colditz Castle]] during [[World War II]] (1942\u20131945)<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.roll-of-honour.com/Bedfordshire/BedfordModernSchoolMemorials.html|title=Roll of Honour \u2013 Bedfordshire \u2013 Bedford Modern School Memorials|work=roll-of-honour.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Captain Richard Howe'', 4 June 1981, p.16</ref>\n* [[Desmond 'Dizzy' de Villiers]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] (1922\u20131976), [[test pilot|chief test pilot]] at [[de Havilland]] and [[English Electric]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\"/>\n\n==Architecture, art and design==\n[[File:Statue of Josiah Conder in the University of Tokyo 0101.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Josiah Conder (architect)|Josiah Conder, statue at the University of Tokyo]]]]\n* [[Josiah Conder (architect)|Josiah Conder]] (1852\u20131920), architect who designed the ''[[Rokumeikan]]'' and other public buildings in Tokyo<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Henry John Sylvester Stannard]] [[Royal Society of British Artists|RBA]] [[Royal Society of Arts|FRSA]] (1870\u20131951), [[Watercolor painting|watercolour]] artist<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n*[[Sydney Morgan Eveleigh]] (1870-1947), architect in Vancouver<ref>H.E. Vipan, 'A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School', (Bedford, no date), p. 38.</ref>\n* [[Hugh Patrick Guarin Maule|Major Hugh Patrick Guarin Maule]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] [[Royal Institute of British Architects|FRIBA]] (1873\u20131940), architect ([[Royal Veterinary College]] in London)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[George Loraine Stampa]] (1875\u20131951), artist, contributor to [[Punch (magazine)|Punch]] and other illustrated papers and magazines<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[W. B. Stonebridge|Walter Stonebridge]] [[Royal Institute of British Architects|FRIBA]] (1879\u20131962), Diocesan Architect for [[Ely, Cambridgeshire|Ely]], [[St Albans]] and [[Bedford]]<ref>{{Cite