{"title_page": "Shirley Setia", "text_new": "{{short description|New Zealand singer and performer}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|Biographies|date=June 2018}}\n{{advert|date=June 2018}}\n{{fanpov|date=March 2017}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Shirley Setia\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Shirley Setia snapped at Miss Diva 2020 Mumbai Preliminary Event (cropped).jpg\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| birth_name       = Shirley \n| birth_date       = 2nd July, 1995\n| birth_place      = Daman, India\n| genre            = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| occupation       = Singer, Actress \n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals|ukulele}}\n| years_active     = 2013 - present\n| website          = {{URL|https://www.shirleysetiaofficial.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Shirley Setia''' is a singer and actress from [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]]. Shirley is making her film debut with ''[[Nikamma]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/all-you-need-to-know-about-nikamma-debutant-shirley-setia/articleshow/70750364.cms|title=All you need to know about 'Nikamma' debutant Shirley Setia - Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nA graduate student from the University of Auckland and marketing and publicity intern at Auckland Council, Setia took part in a contest conducted by [[Super Cassettes Industries T-Series|T-Series]]. Her [[YouTube]] entry was recorded in her bedroom while she was wearing pyjamas.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Joseph |first1=Raveena |title=Meet Youtube sensation Shirley Setia |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/pyjama-popstar/article22375177.ece |accessdate=16 September 2018 |work=The Hindu |date=5 January 2018 |language=en-IN}}</ref> This earned her the nickname \"Pyjama popstar\" by the ''[[New Zealand Herald]]''.<ref name=\"nzherald\">{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11249108 |title=Pyjama pop song a big hit |work=New Zealand Herald |date=4 May 2014 |first=Matthew |last=Theunissen |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> She was declared as one of the winners from thousands of entries. Amidst the chaotic life of being a student and a part-time radio jockey, she started uploading regularly on to YouTube and has since then collaborated with YouTube artists from across US, UK, India, and Canada. Four years, 1.8 million subscribers and 114 M views later, she has now moved to [[Mumbai]] to pursue her dream of making it big in [[Bollywood]]. ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine's Rob Cain wrote a feature on her and her future goals recently in which he stated that \"Bollywood's Next Big Singing Sensation Just Might Be This Tiny Kiwi\".<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2016/03/19/bollywoods-next-big-singing-sensation-just-might-be-this-tiny-kiwi/#587ec16c17f6 |title=Bollywood's Next Big Singing Sensation Just Might Be This Tiny Kiwi |work=Forbes |date=19 March 2016 |first=Rob |last=Cain |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> she was also acknowledged as India's YouTube sensation by the ''[[Hindustan Times]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/this-girl-from-nz-is-the-new-youtube-sensation-for-her-bollywood-covers/story-g9U1emtgjIECvUF4ZbSjSJ.html |title=This girl from NZ is the new YouTube sensation for her Bollywood covers |work=Hindustan Times |date=16 March 2016|accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> and as one of New Zealand's biggest international artists by [[TVNZ]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/shirley-setia-singing-alone-in-grass-field-performing-thousands-fans-india |title=Shirley Setia: From singing alone in a grass field to performing for thousands of fans in India\n |newspaper=TVNZ |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> {{As of|2020|3}}, she has 3.3 million subscribers on YouTube with 244.86 million views.<ref>{{cite web |title=Shirley Setia |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/shirleysetia/about?disable_polymer=1 |website=YouTube |accessdate=26 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nShe was invited by YouTube as a 'YouTube Creator' to perform live in YouTube FanFest held in Mumbai in 2016 and 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mybigplunge.com/life/youtube-fanfest-fastest-growing-online-creators/|title=FanFestLIFE BB Ki Vines, VidyaVox, Technical Guruji among those recognised at YouTube FanFest|last=Cranenburgh|first=Craig|date=23 March 2017|work=Mybigplunge.com|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Award Show\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n|2016\n|BIG Golden Voice\n|BIG Digital Sensation\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.exchange4media.com/industrybriefing/92.7-big-fm-honours-golden-voices-with-prestigious-awards_65794.html |title=92.7 BIG FM honours 'Golden Voices' with prestigious awards |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|Outlook Social Media Awards\n|OSM Musician of the year\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.osm-awards.com/nominee_profile.php?id=MTM3 |title=OSM Awards Winners |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|New Zealand Social Media Award\n|Best in Music\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://smcakl.com/?sid=1024 |title=Winners & Finalists | publisher=NZSMA |accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|Artist Aloud Music Award 2018\n|Best Hindi Music Category\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|2018\n|Social Media Summit & Awards 2018\n|Music Sensation On Social Media\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Film\n!Song\n!Music director\n!Co-singer\n|-\n|2014\n|''Shirley Setia Single Album''\n|\"Thode Se Hum\"\n|Shirley Setia & Abhas Joshi\n|Abhas Joshi\n|-\n|2015\n|''4 Steps Forward''\n|\"Naye Love Ki Subah\"\n|Parichay\n|Parichay & Gunsmith\n|-\n|2016\n|''Shirley Setia Single Album''\n|\"Koi Shor\"\n|Ravi Singhal\n|Ravi Singhal\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Passengers (2016 film)|Passengers]]''\n|\"Aadat\"\n|Sukumar Dutta\n|[[Raftaar (rapper)|Raftaar]], [[Jubin Nautiyal]]\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[A Gentleman]]''\n|\"Disco Disco\"\n|[[Sachin - Jigar]]\n|[[Benny Dayal]]\n|-\n|2017\n|''Best of Luck Laalu''\n|\"Luv u Luv u\"\n|Sachin - Jigar\n|[[Kirtidan Gadhvi]]\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[T-Series (company)|T-Series Mixtape]]''\n|\"Tu Jo Mila-Raabta\"\n|[[Abhijit Vaghani]]\n|Jubin Nautiyal\n|- \n|2017\n|''Shirley Setia Single Album''\n|\"Tu Mil Gaya\"\n|Haroon-Gavin\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|''Jab Koi Baat recreated''\n|\"Jab Koi Baat recreated\"\n|DJ Chetas\n|[[Atif Aslam]]\n|-\n|2018\n|''Gaana Exclusives''\n|\"Koi Vi Nahi\"\n|[[Rajat Nagpal]]\n|Gurnazar Chattha\n|-\n|2018\n|''A Whole New World''\n|\"A Whole New World\"\n|colspan=\"2\"|[[Kurt Hugo Schneider]]\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[5 Weddings]]''\n|\"Na Chah Ke Bhi\"\n|colspan=\"2\"|[[Vishal Mishra (composer)|Vishal Mishra]]\n|-\n|2018\n|''Shirley Setia Single Album''\n|\"Naiyo Jaana\"\n|Ravi Singhal\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[T-Series (company)|T-Series Electrofolk]]''\n|\"Bhumro\"\n|Aditya Dev\n|Aditya Dev, Parry G\n|-\n|2019\n|''Biba - Jio Saavn Original''\n|\"Biba\"\n|[[Marshmello]] & [[Pritam]]\n|Pardeep Singh Sran, [[Dev Negi]]\n|-\n|2019\n|''T-Series Mixtape Season-2''\n|\"Ik Vaari Aa/Naadan Parindey/Tum Ho Toh\"\n|[[Bhushan Kumar]], Ahmed Khan\n|Shirley Setia, [[Abhijit Vaghani|Abhijit V]] & [[Jubin Nautiyal]]\n|}\n\n==Television/Web series==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Shows !! Channel !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2018 || Lockdown || On [[ZEE5]] Originals || Recreating a Hindi Song || Web Reality Show <ref>{{cite news |last1=Zee Media Bureau |title=ZEE5 launches Lockdown with Badshah, Kailash Kher, Raftaar, Jonita Gandhi and many more |url=http://zeenews.india.com/television/zee5-launches-lockdown-with-badshah-kailash-kher-raftaar-jonita-gandhi-and-many-more-2133845.html |accessdate=10 November 2018 |publisher=Zeenews.india.com |date=17 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite 