as wearing pyjamas.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Joseph |first1=Raveena |title=Meet Youtube sensation Shirley Setia |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/pyjama-popstar/article22375177.ece |accessdate=16 September 2018 |work=The Hindu |date=5 January 2018 |language=en-IN}}</ref> This earned her the nickname \"Pyjama popstar\" by the ''[[New Zealand Herald]]''.<ref name=\"nzherald\">{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11249108 |title=Pyjama pop song a big hit |work=New Zealand Herald |date=4 May 2014 |first=Matthew |last=Theunissen |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> She was declared as one of the winners from thousands of entries. Amidst the chaotic life of being a student and a part-time radio jockey, she started uploading regularly on to YouTube and has since then collaborated with YouTube artists from across US, UK, India, and Canada. Four years, 1.8 million subscribers and 114 M views later, she has now moved to [[Mumbai]] to pursue her dream of making it big in [[Bollywood]]. ''[[Forbes]]'' magazine's Rob Cain wrote a feature on her and her future goals recently in which he stated that \"Bollywood's Next Big Singing Sensation Just Might Be This Tiny Kiwi\".<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robcain/2016/03/19/bollywoods-next-big-singing-sensation-just-might-be-this-tiny-kiwi/#587ec16c17f6 |title=Bollywood's Next Big Singing Sensation Just Might Be This Tiny Kiwi |work=Forbes |date=19 March 2016 |first=Rob |last=Cain |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> she was also acknowledged as India's YouTube sensation by the ''[[Hindustan Times]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/this-girl-from-nz-is-the-new-youtube-sensation-for-her-bollywood-covers/story-g9U1emtgjIECvUF4ZbSjSJ.html |title=This girl from NZ is the new YouTube sensation for her Bollywood covers |work=Hindustan Times |date=16 March 2016|accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> and as one of New Zealand's biggest international artists by [[TVNZ]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/shirley-setia-singing-alone-in-grass-field-performing-thousands-fans-india |title=Shirley Setia: From singing alone in a grass field to performing for thousands of fans in India\n |newspaper=TVNZ |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> {{As of|2020|3}}, she has 3.3 million subscribers on YouTube with 244.86 million views.<ref>{{cite web |title=Shirley Setia |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/shirleysetia/about?disable_polymer=1 |website=YouTube |accessdate=26 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nShe was invited by YouTube as a 'YouTube Creator' to perform live in YouTube FanFest held in Mumbai in 2016 and 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mybigplunge.com/life/youtube-fanfest-fastest-growing-online-creators/|title=FanFestLIFE BB Ki Vines, VidyaVox, Technical Guruji among those recognised at YouTube FanFest|last=Cranenburgh|first=Craig|date=23 March 2017|work=Mybigplunge.com|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Award Show\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n|2016\n|BIG Golden Voice\n|BIG Digital Sensation\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.exchange4media.com/industrybriefing/92.7-big-fm-honours-golden-voices-with-prestigious-awards_65794.html |title=92.7 BIG FM honours 'Golden Voices' with prestigious awards |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|Outlook Social Media Awards\n|OSM Musician of the year\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.osm-awards.com/nominee_profile.php?id=MTM3 |title=OSM Awards Winners |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|New Zealand Social Media Award\n|Best in Music\n|{{Won}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://smcakl.com/?sid=1024 |title=Winners & Finalists | publisher=NZSMA |accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|Artist Aloud Music Award 2018\n|Best Hindi Music Category\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|2018\n|Social Media Summit & Awards 2018\n|Music Sensation On Social Media\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n\n== Discography ==\n